<details>
  <summary>You can run this locally as follows</summary>


```bash
## summary with just the declaration names:
./scripts/declarations_diff.sh <optional_commit>

## more verbose report:
./scripts/declarations_diff.sh long <optional_commit>
```
</details>

The doc-module for `script/declarations_diff.sh` contains some details about this script.

---

<details><summary>No changes to technical debt.</summary>

You can run this locally as
```
./scripts/technical-debt-metrics.sh pr_summary
```
* The `relative` value is the weighted *sum* of the differences with weight given by the *inverse* of the current value of the statistic.
* The `absolute` value is the `relative` value divided by the total sum of the inverses of the current values (i.e. the weighted *average* of the differences).
</details>

Here are the [benchmark results](https://speed.lean-lang.org/mathlib4/run-detail/6969fde3-913e-4b3e-b645-a8eddb9daf1d) for commit 2c3df6a7621ee8cb725ada1f30c32034ec6fb56b.Found no runs to compare against.
Here I merged master into `blizzard_inc/fieldify_algebraMap'` and benchmarked but this failed too.

It didn't fail like the original PR does. It just hasn't benchmarked the commit you branched off from master. You can manually compare against another commit or wait until the bot catches up and then manually compare to that.

https://speed.lean-lang.org/mathlib4/compare/e7b27246-a3e6-496a-b552-ff4b45c7236e/to/6969fde3-913e-4b3e-b645-a8eddb9daf1d?hash1=bb6f0a357f5060a95d5460f0efaeb6e42b51359b I believe this is the correct comparison but I should be sanity-checked.
